### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Claims Service – demo script
###
### VS Code REST Client (humao.rest-client)
### Requests are separated by ###
### Named requests (#@name) allow later requests to reference their response
### via {{requestName.response.body.$.fieldPath}}
###
### ClaimRequest body fields:
###   type        String  required (@NotBlank)
###   insuredId   String  required (@NotBlank)
###   description String  optional
###
### Claim response fields:
###   id        String (UUID)
###   type      String
###   status    SUBMITTED | APPROVED | REJECTED
###   insuredId String
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### ── Happy path ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Submit a new claim  (→ 201 CREATED)
# @name submitClaim
POST {{baseUrl}}/claims
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: user:42

{
  "type": "DENTAL",
  "insuredId": "ins-1",
  "description": "Annual check-up and filling"
}

###

### 2. List all claims  (→ 200 OK, array of Claim objects)
GET {{baseUrl}}/claims

###

### 3. Get the submitted claim  (→ 200 OK, status = SUBMITTED)
GET {{baseUrl}}/claims/{{submitClaim.response.body.$.id}}

###

### 4. Approve the claim  (→ 200 OK, status = APPROVED)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/claims/{{submitClaim.response.body.$.id}}/approve
X-User-Id: reviewer:7

###

### 5. Try to approve again  (→ 409 CONFLICT + RFC 7807 ProblemDetail)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/claims/{{submitClaim.response.body.$.id}}/approve
X-User-Id: reviewer:7

###

### ── Error scenarios ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 6. Submit without 'type'  (→ 400 BAD REQUEST + ProblemDetail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/claims
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: user:42

{
  "insuredId": "ins-2",
  "description": "Missing type field"
}

###

### 7. Submit without 'insuredId'  (→ 400 BAD REQUEST + ProblemDetail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/claims
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: user:42

{
  "type": "VISION",
  "description": "Missing insuredId field"
}

###

### 8. Get a non-existent claim  (→ 404 NOT FOUND + ProblemDetail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/claims/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

###

### ── Reject path ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 9. Submit a second claim  (→ 201 CREATED)
# @name submitClaim2
POST {{baseUrl}}/claims
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: user:99

{
  "type": "VISION",
  "insuredId": "ins-2",
  "description": "Contact lenses"
}

###

### 10. Reject the second claim  (→ 200 OK, status = REJECTED)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/claims/{{submitClaim2.response.body.$.id}}/reject
X-User-Id: reviewer:7

###

### 11. Try to reject an already-rejected claim  (→ 409 CONFLICT + ProblemDetail)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/claims/{{submitClaim2.response.body.$.id}}/reject
X-User-Id: reviewer:7
